He can easily glide from 'Bon Ton Roulet' to 'Zydeco Beach Party' to blues, country, conjunto, and back again."

Little Red picked up the accordion at age six and never looked back. He's been making pepper-hot Zydeco music since the 1960s. He's also a master of New Orleans piano styles. Little Red has lived in New Orleans, where he absorbed the musical styles of Clifton Chenier and Professor Longhair; he's performed at the Kennedy Center, the Smithsonian and 10,000 honky tonks from Texas to the Canadian border.

Little Red has been a featured performer at the New Music Seminar in Manhattan and South by SouthWest in Austin. Firmly grounded in the Louisiana sound, his music now transcends all boundaries.
